WEBVTT

00:06.876 --> 00:08.530
This is a first.

00:08.573 --> 00:10.358
Empty service bay
available.

00:10.401 --> 00:11.924
Yeah, it happens.

00:11.968 --> 00:13.404
You know, usually,
when I bring my car in,

00:13.448 --> 00:14.797
I have to leave it
out on the street.

00:14.840 --> 00:16.407
Mm-hmm.
Yeah.

00:16.451 --> 00:17.800
'Cause you're
so busy.

00:17.843 --> 00:19.976
Yup.

00:20.020 --> 00:22.761
Not today, though.

00:22.805 --> 00:24.981
No, not today.

00:26.461 --> 00:27.592
You want to talk
about it?

00:27.636 --> 00:29.594
I do not.

00:31.596 --> 00:32.945
[sighs]

00:32.989 --> 00:35.861
You know
I can't do that.

00:35.905 --> 00:38.647
All right, look, fine.

00:38.690 --> 00:40.823
Business isn't what
it used to be.

00:40.866 --> 00:44.044
And it's not just the
competition from the big chains,

00:44.087 --> 00:45.480
it's all these new cars.

00:45.523 --> 00:48.004
They don't have driveshafts
and differentials,

00:48.048 --> 00:50.920
it's just motherboards
and chips.

00:50.963 --> 00:53.357
It's like riding around
in a big-ass iPad.

00:55.664 --> 00:56.926
Well...

00:56.969 --> 00:58.884
would you like some
constructive criticism?

00:58.928 --> 01:01.539
Oh... Lord.

01:01.583 --> 01:03.498
Look, this place
is a little old-school.

01:03.541 --> 01:05.500
I mean, you don't
even have free Wi-Fi.

01:05.543 --> 01:06.979
Yes, I do.

01:07.023 --> 01:08.981
It's from the Thai place
next door.

01:10.505 --> 01:12.637
The password
is "padthai22."

01:12.681 --> 01:14.813
They tried to change it,
but I figured it out.

01:14.857 --> 01:16.380
[laughs]

01:16.424 --> 01:17.729
Okay.

01:17.773 --> 01:19.470
Have you ever noticed
one of those businesses

01:19.514 --> 01:21.733
that has a sticker
in the window that reads,

01:21.777 --> 01:23.344
"People love us
on Yelp"?

01:24.562 --> 01:26.347
Yeah, but why would I care
about some sticker?

01:26.390 --> 01:28.827
Well, because your customers
care about them.

01:28.871 --> 01:30.481
I use the site
all the time.

01:30.525 --> 01:32.483
In fact, I have
Elite reviewer status,

01:32.527 --> 01:33.484
not to brag.

01:33.528 --> 01:35.095
Don't worry,
you didn't.

01:35.138 --> 01:37.662
Okay, think about this,

01:37.706 --> 01:39.403
would Tina
ever read a book

01:39.447 --> 01:40.752
that didn't have
an Oprah sticker on it?

01:40.796 --> 01:43.059
[chuckling] Hell no.

01:43.103 --> 01:45.714
How would she know
if the book is good?

01:49.500 --> 01:52.590
Ah...

01:52.634 --> 01:54.592
♪ Welcome to the block,
welcome to the neighborhood ♪

01:54.636 --> 01:55.811
♪ Welcome to the hood.

02:00.642 --> 02:03.906
"Since 1989,
Calvin Butler

02:03.949 --> 02:06.343
"has been Pasadena's

02:06.387 --> 02:09.607
"most sought-after
mechanic.

02:09.651 --> 02:13.045
There has even been
talk of a statue."

02:15.787 --> 02:18.703
Whoa, check you out, Pop.What?

02:18.747 --> 02:20.966
You building a Yelp page.
Man, that's pretty ambitious

02:21.010 --> 02:22.838
for a man of your,
uh... [stammers]

02:22.881 --> 02:24.535
...vintage.

02:25.797 --> 02:28.017
Well, I'll have you know
that I'm actually

02:28.060 --> 02:29.714
pretty good
with technology.

02:29.758 --> 02:32.413
See, I got this cool picture
of the shop.

02:32.456 --> 02:35.155
All I have to do is get it off
my phone and onto my computer,

02:35.198 --> 02:37.809
which is easy
because, uh...

02:44.033 --> 02:45.817
Just let me do it.

02:45.861 --> 02:47.384
Oh, I like that idea.

02:47.428 --> 02:49.908
Yeah, there you go.
[chuckles]
Yeah. [mutters]

02:49.952 --> 02:51.954
Hey, man,

02:51.997 --> 02:53.869
I've been thinking,
we should go out

02:53.912 --> 02:55.392
for a night on the town
this week,

02:55.436 --> 02:56.828
like back in the day.
Butler boys.

02:56.872 --> 02:59.788
Oh, yeah, that's
interesting. [laughs]

02:59.831 --> 03:01.572
You know, since the day
you met Necie,

03:01.616 --> 03:04.445
you have asked me to hang out
a total of zero times.

03:05.881 --> 03:07.535
But now that she's out of town,

03:07.578 --> 03:09.406
suddenly,
I'm not invisible anymore.

03:09.450 --> 03:10.581
I know, I know.

03:10.625 --> 03:11.713
I've been
a bad brother.

03:11.756 --> 03:13.193
Yeah.
It's just so weird

03:13.236 --> 03:14.672
with Necie being gone.

03:14.716 --> 03:16.413
I don't know what
to do with myself, man.

03:16.457 --> 03:19.416
For the last six months,
I've been, you know,

03:19.460 --> 03:21.201
busy... every night.

03:22.854 --> 03:24.900
Yes, I know.
I can hear the shrieking.

03:26.467 --> 03:28.208
Thank God Necie
is quiet.

03:30.253 --> 03:31.820
Good Lord, yuck.

03:31.863 --> 03:33.691
[chuckles] I see your yuck,

03:33.735 --> 03:35.954
and raise you a... [shudders]

03:35.998 --> 03:37.739
Okay, it has been a minute

03:37.782 --> 03:39.480
since I hit the clubs.

03:39.523 --> 03:41.960
We should take two
separate cars 'cause, uh,

03:42.004 --> 03:44.093
you know how
your boy does. [laughs]

03:44.136 --> 03:45.877
[forced laugh]

03:45.921 --> 03:48.619
No, we don't.
Let's keep it that way.

03:50.491 --> 03:52.493
Here, Pops,
your picture is uploaded.

03:52.536 --> 03:55.104
Ah, cool. All right.

03:55.147 --> 03:57.628
And...

03:57.672 --> 04:00.631
Calvin's Yelp page
is ready to launch.

04:00.675 --> 04:03.112
All right.
This is exciting.

04:03.155 --> 04:05.201
Okay, ten... nine...

04:05.245 --> 04:06.898
eight...
And post.
[laptop chimes]

04:06.942 --> 04:08.857
Dad,

04:08.900 --> 04:10.467
you got to respect
the countdown, man.

04:10.511 --> 04:12.730
Marty, I ain't got
time to waste.

04:12.774 --> 04:14.602
I'm trying to get me a sticker.

04:17.996 --> 04:19.650
So...

04:19.694 --> 04:22.174
you about ready
to close that thing?

04:22.218 --> 04:24.655
Almost.

04:26.701 --> 04:29.051
You know, writing a
Yelp review is tricky.
[sighs]

04:29.094 --> 04:31.749
There's a fine line between rave
and going over the top.

04:31.793 --> 04:33.490
Oh, there's also
a fine line between

04:33.534 --> 04:35.710
sex and me
going to sleep.

04:35.753 --> 04:38.495
Stay with me, baby.
I'm almost done.

04:38.539 --> 04:40.497
[groans] Just give him
five stars

04:40.541 --> 04:42.543
and take
your pants off.

04:42.586 --> 04:45.023
Look, you know,
it's not that simple.

04:45.067 --> 04:47.983
I take the integrity of my
Yelp reviews very seriously.

04:48.026 --> 04:50.072
There are legions
of Yelpers out there

04:50.115 --> 04:53.641
who have come to trust
the reviews of "Dave J."

04:54.859 --> 04:56.861
That is 100%
in your head.

04:56.905 --> 04:58.298
Is it?

04:58.341 --> 05:00.952
I gave one star to a bike shop
that bent my frame.

05:00.996 --> 05:03.912
36 people found
that review "helpful."

05:05.174 --> 05:08.525
That bike shop
is now a dentist office.

05:08.569 --> 05:12.050
Mmm. That kind of power
is a turn-on.

05:12.094 --> 05:13.225
Is it?

05:13.269 --> 05:15.184
No, but it's 11:15, so

05:15.227 --> 05:17.273
yes.O-Okay.

05:19.319 --> 05:22.322
CHILDREN [singing off-key]:
♪ This little light of

05:22.365 --> 05:25.586
♪ Mine

05:25.629 --> 05:27.544
♪ I'm gonna let it... Ugh.

05:27.588 --> 05:29.851
Hey, Tina. Thanks
for picking me up.

05:29.894 --> 05:33.768
What in the Fergie's national
anthem is going on in there?

05:33.811 --> 05:36.161
It's the after-school
music program.

05:36.205 --> 05:37.772
We lost our music teacher
last year,

05:37.815 --> 05:39.556
so the biology teacher
is filling in.

05:39.600 --> 05:42.646
Well, what, is he dissecting
a live goat in there?

05:44.039 --> 05:45.562
It's not that bad.

05:45.606 --> 05:48.739
[children wailing-singing]

05:48.783 --> 05:50.915
Okay, it's terrible.
Mm.

05:50.959 --> 05:52.264
I'm looking to hire
someone new,

05:52.308 --> 05:54.005
but it's a really hard
position to fill.

05:54.049 --> 05:56.356
I need someone
who can sing and dance

05:56.399 --> 05:57.792
and has the charisma

05:57.835 --> 06:00.098
to inspire the kids.

06:00.142 --> 06:01.622
And pretty.

06:04.102 --> 06:06.757
Gemma, how gullible
do you think I am?

06:06.801 --> 06:09.325
What? Why would you--
Wh-Wh-What?

06:10.370 --> 06:13.634
[imitating Gemma]: "Hey, T.
Thanks for picking me up.

06:13.677 --> 06:16.724
Meet me in front
of multipurpose room three."

06:16.767 --> 06:19.944
You knew damn well I was gonna
walk in and hear all that mess.

06:19.988 --> 06:23.165
Whoa. You think--
Wh-- Uh, what?

06:25.776 --> 06:26.864
Will you do it?

06:26.908 --> 06:28.213
[smacks lips]

06:28.257 --> 06:30.651
Gemma, you know I've got
my cupcake business and...

06:30.694 --> 06:32.870
But it's only a couple
of afternoons a week.

06:32.914 --> 06:34.916
[sighs]
But you know what?

06:34.959 --> 06:36.221
I shouldn't have
put you on the spot.

06:36.265 --> 06:38.093
Yeah, you
shouldn't have.

06:38.136 --> 06:40.225
Oh, hi, Miss Tina.
Hey.

06:40.269 --> 06:41.966
I wasn't expecting
to see you here.

06:44.186 --> 06:46.406
Can we
go home, Mom?

06:46.449 --> 06:47.711
I'm sad.

06:47.755 --> 06:49.800
This is making all the kids
fall out of love

06:49.844 --> 06:51.672
with music.
Oh.

06:55.676 --> 06:58.809
The only thing worse than
that singing is y'all's acting.

06:58.853 --> 07:00.724
I'll take that
as a yes.

07:00.768 --> 07:03.205
All right.
[shrieks]

07:05.033 --> 07:07.644
Mm-hmm. Mm...

07:07.688 --> 07:09.733
Mm-hmm...

07:09.777 --> 07:11.996
So...?
It's good, right?

07:12.040 --> 07:13.824
No, it's great. [chuckles]

07:13.868 --> 07:16.174
Real rave. Five stars.

07:16.218 --> 07:18.046
Happy to do it.

07:18.089 --> 07:20.222
[stammers] There's one line
in here that,

07:20.265 --> 07:21.702
uh, you know,
threw me off a little.

07:21.745 --> 07:24.269
"Don't be put off

07:24.313 --> 07:26.446
"by the owner's
prickly exterior,

07:26.489 --> 07:29.666
you'll come to realize
he's a great guy."

07:29.710 --> 07:31.189
Yeah.

07:31.233 --> 07:34.236
Why-why did you call me
"prickly"?

07:34.279 --> 07:36.978
Well, the takeaway is

07:37.021 --> 07:38.893
"great guy."

07:38.936 --> 07:40.460
Yeah, yeah, yeah, sure,

07:40.503 --> 07:43.375
but before that it's "prickly."

07:44.812 --> 07:48.424
Okay, look, Calvin, don't
take this as an insult, but,

07:48.468 --> 07:50.861
you know, I didn't want my
followers to come in and be...

07:50.905 --> 07:54.430
caught off guard by your...
strong personality.

07:54.474 --> 07:57.738
But, again, "great guy."

07:57.781 --> 08:01.263
I appreciate
the review, Dave,

08:01.306 --> 08:04.396
but, come on, I'm not prickly.

08:08.009 --> 08:09.401
Oh, I agree, Pop.

08:09.445 --> 08:10.446
You're not prickly.

08:10.490 --> 08:11.795
Thank you.

08:11.839 --> 08:13.754
Yeah, that's not
the right word.

08:13.797 --> 08:16.278
It's more like...
cantankerous.
[chuckles]

08:17.453 --> 08:19.368
Testy.

08:19.411 --> 08:20.500
Cranky.

08:20.543 --> 08:22.240
Ooh, you know,
I considered cranky.

08:22.284 --> 08:25.069
Ah.
Ooh, you know what?
I got it:

08:25.113 --> 08:26.331
obstreperous.

08:26.375 --> 08:28.943
Oh, yeah.
Obstreperous.
No, no, no, no.

08:28.986 --> 08:30.814
I am not obstreperous.

08:30.858 --> 08:33.295
I'm the opposite.
I am very streperous.

08:34.949 --> 08:36.516
Calvin, you know, you're
only focusing on the negative.

08:36.559 --> 08:37.734
Look at this.

08:37.778 --> 08:41.172
18 thumbs up for Dave J.
I'm killing it.

08:42.217 --> 08:44.436
But the important
thing is-is

08:44.480 --> 08:46.438
I'm bringing eyeballs
to your site.

08:46.482 --> 08:49.920
Yes, and all the eyeballs
are agreeing with you.

08:49.964 --> 08:52.836
"The owner is definitely
on the prickly side."

08:54.098 --> 08:57.362
Oh, ooh, oh, look at,
"Watch out for Mr. Grumpy."

08:58.625 --> 09:00.801
Look, these are all
five-star reviews, though.

09:00.844 --> 09:02.759
This is how
you earn the sticker.

09:02.803 --> 09:04.021
Ooh, "crusty."

09:04.065 --> 09:06.937
Ooh, yup, yup.
"Crotchety."

